// Content Sprint 3.
window.CONTENT_SPRINT_3 = {"production-sandbox":{"summary":"Use Production for live marketplace operation and Sandbox for training, configuration and end-to-end testing. Keep each environment clearly identified, test changes safely and verify approved settings in Production.","audience":["Marketplace operations","Environment Managers","Catalogue","Seller onboarding","Finance","Customer service","Technology and integrations"],"sections":{"About Your Marketplacer Environments":"<p>Marketplacer Delivery creates and preconfigures a Production environment and a Sandbox environment during onboarding. Production is the live marketplace. Sandbox is the controlled environment for learning, configuration and testing.</p><div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Area</th><th>Production</th><th>Sandbox</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Purpose</td><td>Live marketplace operation</td><td>Training, configuration and testing</td></tr><tr><td>Sellers and products</td><td>Live Seller accounts, Adverts and Variants</td><td>Test records and anonymised Production data</td></tr><tr><td>Orders and finance</td><td>Real Orders, Refund Requests and Remittances</td><td>Test workflows and calculations</td></tr><tr><td>Integrations</td><td>Production endpoints and credentials</td><td>Test endpoints and credentials</td></tr><tr><td>Incident priority</td><td>Assessed as live business impact</td><td>Assessed as non-production impact</td></tr></tbody></table></div><p>Use Sandbox to validate the intended setup, record the approved result, apply it in Production and verify the live outcome.</p><div class=\"process-flow\"><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">1</span><strong>Confirm the marketplace decision</strong></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">2</span><strong>Configure and test in Sandbox</strong></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">3</span><strong>Apply the approved result in Production</strong></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">4</span><strong>Verify and record evidence</strong></div></div>","Production":"<p>Production is the authoritative live environment. Changes can affect live Sellers, products, Orders, refunds, communications, integrations and financial calculations.</p><h3>Use Production for</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Approved marketplace configuration</li><li>Live Seller creation and product onboarding</li><li>Customer Orders and Seller fulfilment</li><li>Live cancellations, returns and Refund Requests</li><li>Commission, Remittance and payout operations</li><li>Production integrations and reporting</li></ul><h3>Before applying a change</h3><ol><li>Confirm the approved business decision.</li><li>Check that the Production environment is open.</li><li>Understand the affected workflow and connected systems.</li><li>Complete Sandbox testing where practical.</li><li>Prepare verification steps and a correction approach.</li><li>Confirm that the person making the change has the required permission.</li></ol><h3>After applying a change</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Confirm the saved value</li><li>Run the affected workflow</li><li>Check connected-system behaviour</li><li>Review notifications and reporting</li><li>Record the owner, date, result and evidence</li></ul><div class=\"callout warning\"><strong>Keep live test data to a minimum.</strong> Production records can remain in operational queues, reporting and financial processes. Use controlled records and minimal values where Production validation is required.</div>","Sandbox":"<p>Sandbox is the primary environment for training, configuration testing and process rehearsal.</p><h3>Use Sandbox for</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Operator and Seller Portal training</li><li>Test Seller creation</li><li>Sample Advert and Variant ingestion</li><li>Taxonomy, mapping, Catalog Rule and vetting tests</li><li>Order, Shipment, cancellation and return scenarios</li><li>API, webhook and MConnect testing</li><li>Issue reproduction and internal procedure development</li></ul><h3>Use recognisable test data</h3><p>Use clear names such as <code>TEST Seller - Footwear</code>, <code>TEST Product - Refund Scenario</code> and <code>TEST User - Catalogue Reviewer</code>. This helps teams separate test activity from copied Production records.</p><div class=\"callout note\"><strong>Sandbox data is temporary.</strong> A refresh replaces Sandbox data with an anonymised Production copy. Record test setup, export required evidence and keep repeatable scripts outside the environment.</div>","Sandbox Email Routing":"<p>System-generated Sandbox emails are redirected to Marketplacer-managed test inboxes so test activity does not contact live Sellers, customers or Operator users.</p><p>This includes welcome emails, password setup, recovery codes, password resets, Order notifications, refund messages, Remittance messages and other transactional emails.</p><h3>Configure an internal copy recipient</h3><p>Navigate to:</p><p><code>Configuration &gt; Site Details &gt; Account Emails &gt; Staging Email CC</code></p><p>Add a monitored team address. The nominated address receives a copy of Sandbox emails and can forward account-access messages to the approved tester.</p><ol><li>Open <strong>Configuration &gt; Site Details</strong> in Sandbox.</li><li>Locate <strong>Account Emails</strong>.</li><li>Enter the nominated address in <strong>Staging Email CC</strong>.</li><li>Save the setting.</li><li>Create or reset a test user.</li><li>Confirm the copied email reaches the nominated inbox.</li></ol><div class=\"callout note\"><strong>Marketplacer can assist before this is configured.</strong> During onboarding, your Delivery Manager can help locate and forward a Sandbox email. Marketplacer Support can assist after handover.</div>","Accessing the Correct Environment":"<p>Production and Sandbox have separate environment-specific URLs. Bookmark them with clear names such as <strong>Marketplacer - Production</strong> and <strong>Marketplacer - Sandbox</strong>.</p><h3>Check before changing a record</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Browser address and environment indicator</li><li>Marketplace name</li><li>Seller and record name</li><li>Live or test status</li><li>Production or test integration endpoint</li><li>Whether an email could reach a live recipient</li></ul><div class=\"callout decision\"><strong>Use a quick confirmation prompt.</strong> Which environment am I in, what record am I changing and who or what could be affected?</div>","Choosing Where to Work":"<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Activity</th><th>Recommended environment</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Learn the Operator Portal or train a new user</td><td>Sandbox</td></tr><tr><td>Test a setting, Seller, product or workflow</td><td>Sandbox</td></tr><tr><td>Develop an API, webhook or MConnect connection</td><td>Sandbox with test endpoints</td></tr><tr><td>Create an approved live Seller</td><td>Production</td></tr><tr><td>Onboard live Seller products</td><td>Production</td></tr><tr><td>Process real customer and Seller activity</td><td>Production</td></tr><tr><td>Reproduce a live issue safely</td><td>Sandbox where practical</td></tr><tr><td>Complete final launch validation</td><td>Controlled Production testing</td></tr></tbody></table></div><p>For an urgent live issue, assess the impact, apply the smallest appropriate correction, verify immediately and document the outcome.</p>","Keeping Environments Aligned":"<p>Sandbox and Production will not always be identical. Record intentional differences and confirm that approved live configuration is present in Production.</p><div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Normally aligned</th><th>May intentionally differ</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Taxonomy, Prototypes and Option Types</td><td>Test Sellers and products</td></tr><tr><td>Finance, Seller and product-governance settings</td><td>Test Orders and Refund Requests</td></tr><tr><td>Refund Reasons and shipping rules</td><td>Webhooks and integration endpoints</td></tr><tr><td>Operator roles and core access model</td><td>Payment test credentials</td></tr><tr><td>Approved branding and business details</td><td>Staging Email CC and email suppression</td></tr></tbody></table></div><h3>Maintain a configuration register</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Setting and navigation path</li><li>Decision owner</li><li>Sandbox status</li><li>Production status</li><li>Intentional difference</li><li>Evidence and last review date</li></ul><p>Before go-live, compare both environments and confirm that Production contains every approved launch setting without unintended Sandbox-only values.</p>","Preparing for Sandbox Refreshes":"<p>Before a refresh, review active tests, retain required evidence, record webhooks and MConnect settings, notify affected teams and assign post-refresh actions.</p><p>After a refresh, confirm access, recreate webhooks, reconnect MConnect, restore test endpoints, verify Staging Email CC and run smoke tests.</p><h3>Related Marketplacer articles</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/40342909631757-Sandbox-environment-sync\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Sandbox environment sync</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/41613069016973-Understand-webhook-removal-during-data-refreshes\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Understand webhook removal during data refreshes</a></li></ul>"},"related":[["sandbox-refreshes","Sandbox Refreshes"],["access-authentication","Access and Authentication"],["configuration-testing","Marketplace Configuration Testing"]]},"sandbox-refreshes":{"summary":"Prepare for the weekly Sandbox refresh, understand which records and connections are replaced, and restore the environment safely before testing resumes.","audience":["Marketplace operations","Environment Managers","Technology and integrations","Catalogue","Seller onboarding","Testing teams"],"sections":{"How a Sandbox Refresh Works":"<p>A Sandbox refresh replaces the current Sandbox database with an anonymised copy of Production. The process is a replacement, not a merge, so Sandbox-only records and configuration can be removed.</p><div class=\"process-flow\"><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">1</span><strong>Current Sandbox is replaced</strong></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">2</span><strong>Production data is copied and anonymised</strong></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">3</span><strong>External connections are cleared where required</strong></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">4</span><strong>Post-refresh setup is completed</strong></div></div><p>A refreshed Sandbox provides a recent baseline for realistic testing while protecting customer and sensitive information.</p>","Weekly Refresh Schedule":"<p>The standard refresh runs weekly, typically every Saturday at approximately 3:00 AM AEST. Plan multi-day testing around this window.</p><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Complete or document active scenarios before the refresh</li><li>Export evidence that must be retained</li><li>Notify teams whose work will be interrupted</li><li>Allow time for reconnection and smoke testing</li><li>Schedule formal testing only after the environment is ready</li></ul><div class=\"callout note\"><strong>Confirm the current schedule for your marketplace.</strong> Marketplacer may update operational schedules. Check the Sandbox sync article or confirm with Support when timing is critical.</div>","What Is Replaced or Cleared":"<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Area</th><th>Refresh behaviour</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Products and Orders</td><td>Sandbox records are overwritten by the anonymised Production copy</td></tr><tr><td>Users and credentials</td><td>Production users and credentials are copied into Sandbox</td></tr><tr><td>Marketplacer API keys</td><td>Copied from Production</td></tr><tr><td>Webhooks</td><td>Sandbox definitions are cleared and Production webhooks are not copied</td></tr><tr><td>MConnect</td><td>Sandbox connections and configuration are cleared</td></tr><tr><td>Third-party credentials</td><td>May be removed or require reconnection for safety</td></tr><tr><td>Sandbox-only data</td><td>Removed if it does not exist in Production</td></tr></tbody></table></div><h3>Sandbox emails</h3><p>Verify <code>Configuration &gt; Site Details &gt; Account Emails &gt; Staging Email CC</code> after the refresh so account and transactional test emails remain visible to your team.</p>","Before a Refresh":"<h3>Review active work</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Tests in progress</li><li>Open defects being reproduced</li><li>Training and demonstrations</li><li>Integration work</li><li>Records required to complete a scenario</li></ul><h3>Capture configuration and evidence</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Webhook URLs, events and authentication headers</li><li>MConnect connection and import settings</li><li>External test credentials and endpoints</li><li>Test Seller, Advert, Order and Refund Request setup</li><li>Screenshots, reports, payloads and expected outcomes</li></ul><h3>Notify affected teams</h3><p>Share the expected timing, testing pause, recovery actions and named owner for each task.</p>","After a Refresh":"<ol><li>Confirm required users can sign in with Production credentials.</li><li>Review the copied Production baseline.</li><li>Recreate Sandbox webhooks under <strong>Configuration &gt; Webhooks</strong>.</li><li>Reconnect and configure MConnect test stores.</li><li>Restore payment and third-party test connections.</li><li>Verify <strong>Staging Email CC</strong>.</li><li>Recreate required test data.</li><li>Run smoke tests before formal testing resumes.</li></ol><h3>Smoke-test the flow</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>User login</li><li>Product creation or import</li><li>Mapping and product vetting</li><li>Order creation</li><li>Seller Invoice and Shipment</li><li>Refund Request</li><li>Email delivery to the Staging Email CC</li><li>Webhook delivery to the test endpoint</li></ul>","Requesting an Additional Refresh":"<p>Submit a Marketplacer Support request where a launch-critical or troubleshooting need cannot wait for the regular refresh.</p><h3>Include</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Marketplace and Sandbox URL</li><li>Reason and required timeframe</li><li>Testing or project impact</li><li>Confirmation that Sandbox-only data can be replaced</li><li>Teams affected</li><li>Webhooks and integrations that will be rebuilt</li></ul><div class=\"callout warning\"><strong>Capture active work first.</strong> A refresh cannot preserve selected Sandbox-only records while replacing the rest of the environment.</div>","Troubleshooting After a Refresh":"<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Issue</th><th>First checks</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>User cannot sign in</td><td>Use Production credentials, confirm the user exists in Production and verify the Sandbox URL</td></tr><tr><td>Webhook stopped</td><td>Recreate it under Configuration > Webhooks and use the approved test endpoint</td></tr><tr><td>MConnect is disconnected</td><td>Reconnect the test store and restore the recorded settings</td></tr><tr><td>Test records disappeared</td><td>Recreate them from the test script</td></tr><tr><td>Emails are not visible</td><td>Check Staging Email CC and the nominated inbox</td></tr><tr><td>Environment seems incomplete</td><td>Compare with Production, collect evidence and submit a Support request</td></tr></tbody></table></div><h3>Related Marketplacer articles</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/40342909631757-Sandbox-environment-sync\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Sandbox environment sync</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/41613069016973-Understand-webhook-removal-during-data-refreshes\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Understand webhook removal during data refreshes</a></li></ul>"},"related":[["production-sandbox","Production and Sandbox"],["webhooks","Webhooks"],["mconnect","MConnect"]]},"access-authentication":{"summary":"Set up secure individual access to Production and Sandbox, choose the appropriate authentication method, complete first-time login and prepare account-recovery and access-review processes.","audience":["Environment Managers","Full Administrators","Marketplace operations","Technology and security","Operator Portal users"],"sections":{"Understanding Access and Authentication":"<p>Each person should have an individual Operator team-member account. Individual access supports role assignment, activity traceability, secure recovery and prompt removal when responsibilities change.</p><div class=\"card-grid\"><article class=\"info-card\"><h3>Authentication</h3><p>Confirms who the person is through a Marketplacer username and password or SAML single sign-on.</p></article><article class=\"info-card\"><h3>Authorisation</h3><p>Controls what the person can view and manage through the assigned Operator role.</p></article></div><p>Confirm whether each user needs Production, Sandbox or both. Training and configuration testing can usually begin in Sandbox before Production access is granted.</p>","Authentication Methods":"<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Method</th><th>Suitable use</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Marketplacer username and password</td><td>Local users, contractors, emergency administrators and environments without SSO</td></tr><tr><td>SAML single sign-on</td><td>Organisations centralising authentication, MFA, provisioning and deactivation</td></tr><tr><td>Combined model</td><td>Most staff use SSO while a controlled local administrator account supports emergency access</td></tr></tbody></table></div><p>For SSO users, the Identity Provider manages authentication and MFA. Retain a controlled local administrator account where your security policy permits it and an SSO outage would otherwise block all access.</p>","First-Time Login":"<h3>Create the team member</h3><p>Navigate to:</p><p><code>Configuration &gt; User Roles &amp; Permissions &gt; Manage Team Members</code></p><ol><li>Select <strong>New Team Member</strong>.</li><li>Enter the person’s name, username, email and mobile number with country code.</li><li>Assign the approved Operator role.</li><li>Create the account.</li><li>Ask the user to complete password and MFA setup.</li><li>Verify access to the correct environment and functions.</li></ol><h3>Sandbox account emails</h3><p>Welcome emails, password setup and recovery codes are redirected to Marketplacer-managed test inboxes. Configure <code>Configuration &gt; Site Details &gt; Account Emails &gt; Staging Email CC</code> so your team receives a copy.</p><div class=\"contextual-walkthroughs\"><h3>Platform walkthrough</h3><a class=\"contextual-walkthrough-link\" href=\"https://www.loom.com/share/09026785de194119a1fbe3ce00474144?sid=cc6ef429-77dc-494b-b5ae-14b5e29da774\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><span>Logging into Marketplacer</span><strong>Watch walkthrough</strong></a></div>","Multi-Factor Authentication":"<p>Local Marketplacer accounts can use SMS, an authenticator application or a passkey for the second authentication step.</p><div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Method</th><th>Setup path or action</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>SMS</td><td>Use the mobile number stored on the team-member account</td></tr><tr><td>Authenticator application</td><td>Profile icon > My Details & Password > Multi-Factor Authentication</td></tr><tr><td>Passkey</td><td>Profile icon > My Details & Password > Multi-Factor Authentication</td></tr><tr><td>Passwordless passkey login</td><td>Configuration > Authentication Settings, where enabled</td></tr></tbody></table></div><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Keep phone details current</li><li>Store recovery codes in an approved password manager or security vault</li><li>Remove lost or unused authenticators</li><li>Report a lost device promptly</li><li>Review unexpected login requests as a security event</li></ul>","Single Sign-On":"<p>SSO connects Marketplacer to your SAML Identity Provider. Create a separate application definition for Production and Sandbox because each environment has its own sign-in context.</p><p>Navigate to:</p><p><code>Configuration &gt; SSO Identity Providers</code></p><ol><li>Create the Marketplacer application in the Identity Provider.</li><li>Use email address as the SAML NameID.</li><li>Prepare the metadata URL or XML.</li><li>Configure name and role attributes where required.</li><li>Add the Identity Provider in Marketplacer.</li><li>Test with a controlled user before wider rollout.</li></ol><p>Service-provider metadata and certificates are available under <code>Configuration &gt; SSO Configuration</code>.</p><div class=\"callout decision\"><strong>Confirm role ownership before enabling automatic updates.</strong> Identity Provider role values must align with the exact Marketplacer role names.</div>","Passwords, Recovery Codes and Account Recovery":"<h3>Password reset</h3><p>Use <strong>Forgotten your password</strong> on the Operator Portal login page. In Sandbox, retrieve the copied reset email through the Staging Email CC inbox.</p><h3>Recovery codes</h3><p>An authorised administrator can refresh codes under:</p><p><code>Configuration &gt; User Roles &amp; Permissions &gt; Manage Team Members &gt; Edit</code></p><p>Refreshing codes replaces the existing set. Store the new codes securely.</p><h3>Lost authentication device</h3><ol><li>Verify the user’s identity through your internal security process.</li><li>Use an available recovery method.</li><li>Remove the lost authenticator or passkey.</li><li>Update the authorised MFA destination.</li><li>Refresh recovery codes where appropriate.</li><li>Review recent activity if compromise is possible.</li></ol>","Managing Access Across Environments":"<p>Maintain separate access decisions for Production and Sandbox. Sandbox may include trainees, testers and implementation partners, while Production should be limited to live operational responsibilities.</p><h3>Joiner, mover and leaver process</h3><div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Stage</th><th>Required action</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Joiner</td><td>Approve the business need, create or provision the user, assign the role, test and record access</td></tr><tr><td>Mover</td><td>Remove permissions no longer required, assign the new role and verify the change</td></tr><tr><td>Leaver</td><td>Remove SSO assignment and local access, transfer ownership and review related credentials</td></tr></tbody></table></div><p>Review Full Admin, local accounts outside SSO, finance permissions, API keys and webhook access at an agreed recurring interval.</p><h3>Related Marketplacer articles</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/360004000232-Sign-into-your-account\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Sign into your account</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/10549432905229-Manage-single-sign-on-SSO-Identity-Providers\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Manage single sign-on Identity Providers</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/31439376204941-Use-authenticator-apps-and-passkeys-for-Multi-Factor-Authentication-MFA-in-the-Operator-Portal\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Use authenticator apps and passkeys for MFA</a></li></ul>"},"related":[["team-permissions","Team Members and Permissions"],["production-sandbox","Production and Sandbox"],["getting-support","Getting Support"]]},"team-permissions":{"summary":"Create individual Operator accounts, assign standard or custom roles, test permission dependencies and maintain access as responsibilities change.","audience":["Environment Managers","Full Administrators","Marketplace operations","Security and technology","Finance","Catalogue","Customer service"],"sections":{"Understanding Team Members and Roles":"<p>An Operator team member is an employee, contractor or authorised partner who needs the Operator Portal. Seller users, customer accounts and API clients are managed separately.</p><p>Use the current paths:</p><p><code>Configuration &gt; User Roles &amp; Permissions &gt; Manage Team Members</code><br><code>Configuration &gt; User Roles &amp; Permissions &gt; Manage Roles &amp; Permissions</code></p><p>The team-member account stores identity and authentication details. The assigned role controls visible functions and permitted actions.</p>","Planning Team Access":"<p>Start with the person’s work, then select the permissions required to complete it.</p><ol><li>Identify the business responsibilities.</li><li>Confirm whether Production, Sandbox or both are required.</li><li>List the pages, reports and actions needed.</li><li>Identify sensitive actions that require separate approval.</li><li>Select a standard role or create a custom role.</li><li>Test the role in Sandbox.</li></ol><div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Team</th><th>Typical activities</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Marketplace operations</td><td>Sellers, Orders, Refund Requests, configuration and operational reporting</td></tr><tr><td>Seller management</td><td>Seller accounts, onboarding, chat and performance</td></tr><tr><td>Catalogue</td><td>Adverts, vetting, Catalog Rules, taxonomy and Golden Products</td></tr><tr><td>Customer service</td><td>Orders, Shipments and Refund Requests</td></tr><tr><td>Finance</td><td>Sales reports, Remittances, fees and payouts</td></tr><tr><td>Technology</td><td>API keys, webhooks, SSO and integration troubleshooting</td></tr></tbody></table></div>","Managing Team Members":"<p>Navigate to <code>Configuration &gt; User Roles &amp; Permissions &gt; Manage Team Members</code>.</p><h3>Create</h3><ol><li>Select <strong>New Team Member</strong>.</li><li>Enter the required identity and contact details.</li><li>Assign the approved role.</li><li>Create the account.</li><li>Complete first-time login and verify access.</li></ol><h3>Edit</h3><p>Use <strong>Edit</strong> to update account details, mobile number, role or recovery codes.</p><h3>Remove</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Confirm the approved removal request</li><li>Transfer operational ownership</li><li>Remove SSO assignment where applicable</li><li>Delete the local team member</li><li>Review API keys or integrations owned by the person</li><li>Record completion</li></ul><div class=\"contextual-walkthroughs\"><h3>Platform walkthroughs</h3><a class=\"contextual-walkthrough-link\" href=\"https://www.loom.com/share/0bbe87bd00944e008c0752df67cd8c3c?sid=23b3d5cc-3d7c-42b8-89fc-2128056c3e09\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><span>Creating a new team member</span><strong>Watch walkthrough</strong></a><a class=\"contextual-walkthrough-link\" href=\"https://www.loom.com/share/c29e4c30e10345408b29021f8df36ad9?sid=ea87d697-e44d-40ed-9724-752175289816\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><span>Creating user roles</span><strong>Watch walkthrough</strong></a></div>","Standard Operator Roles":"<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Role</th><th>General purpose</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Customer Support</td><td>Customer, Order and refund investigation</td></tr><tr><td>Marketing</td><td>Selected marketplace, product and sales information</td></tr><tr><td>Finance</td><td>Financial, Order, reporting and billing functions</td></tr><tr><td>Webmaster</td><td>Broad platform access with selected sensitive restrictions</td></tr><tr><td>Full Admin</td><td>All Operator Portal areas and team-member administration</td></tr></tbody></table></div><p>Review the effective permissions before assignment. A role name may not match the way your organisation divides responsibility.</p><div class=\"callout warning\"><strong>Reserve Full Admin for a small authorised group.</strong> Use narrower roles for routine operations, catalogue, finance, refunds and integrations.</div>","Custom Operator Roles":"<p>Navigate to <code>Configuration &gt; User Roles &amp; Permissions &gt; Manage Roles &amp; Permissions</code>.</p><ol><li>Select <strong>Create a role</strong>.</li><li>Enter a clear role name and description.</li><li>Select the required permissions.</li><li>Review sensitive permissions and dependencies.</li><li>Create the role.</li><li>Test it with a controlled Sandbox user.</li><li>Assign it after approval.</li></ol><h3>Use clear names</h3><p>Examples include <code>Marketplace Operations</code>, <code>Catalogue Reviewer</code>, <code>Refund Processor</code>, <code>Finance Reporting</code> and <code>Integration Administrator</code>.</p><p>A role name cannot be changed after creation. Its description and permissions can be updated.</p>","Permission Groups":"<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Group</th><th>Examples of controlled access</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Sellers</td><td>Create and manage Sellers, chat, performance and login as Seller</td></tr><tr><td>Orders</td><td>View, export and manage Orders and payout actions</td></tr><tr><td>Refunds</td><td>View requests, process returns, process refunds and revert denial</td></tr><tr><td>Products</td><td>Catalogue, vetting, Catalog Rules and Golden Products</td></tr><tr><td>Reporting</td><td>Sales, Remittances, fees, mail log, Activity Logs and Problem Reports</td></tr><tr><td>Categorisation</td><td>Categories, Brands, Prototypes and Option Types</td></tr><tr><td>Configuration</td><td>Site, Seller, product, finance, refund and shipping settings</td></tr><tr><td>APIs and webhooks</td><td>API keys, GraphQL access, webhooks and authentication settings</td></tr><tr><td>User management</td><td>Team members, roles, SSO and Full Admin grants</td></tr></tbody></table></div><div class=\"callout warning\"><strong>Review high-impact permissions individually.</strong> Login as Seller, final refund processing, payout approval, API key creation, webhooks, SSO and user management should be restricted to trained users with a clear operational need.</div>","Assigning and Testing Roles":"<ol><li>Create a controlled Sandbox user.</li><li>Assign the proposed role.</li><li>Review the visible navigation.</li><li>Open each required page.</li><li>Complete the required actions, not only page viewing.</li><li>Confirm unrelated sensitive functions are unavailable.</li><li>Test permission dependencies.</li><li>Record the result and approve the role.</li></ol><p>Examples of complete task tests include starting and finalising a Refund Request, approving an Advert, exporting a report, creating an API key or saving a configuration change.</p>","Reviewing and Changing Access":"<p>Review access before go-live, after organisational changes, when a contractor finishes, after a security incident and at a recurring interval.</p><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Active and dormant users</li><li>Full Admin access</li><li>Local accounts outside SSO</li><li>Production access</li><li>Finance and refund permissions</li><li>API key and webhook permissions</li><li>User-management permissions</li><li>Temporary access and expiry dates</li></ul><h3>Maintain an access register</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Team member and business function</li><li>Production and Sandbox access</li><li>Authentication method</li><li>Assigned role</li><li>Sensitive permissions</li><li>Approver, grant date, review date and expiry date</li></ul><h3>Related Marketplacer articles</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/28925798056333-Create-and-manage-Operator-user-roles\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Create and manage Operator user roles</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/28925785268365-Operator-user-role-permissions\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Operator user role permissions</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/360003820732-Create-Operator-team-members\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Create Operator team members</a></li></ul>"},"related":[["access-authentication","Access and Authentication"],["roles-responsibilities","Roles and Responsibilities"],["production-readiness","Production Readiness"]]},"site-branding":{"summary":"Configure the marketplace identity, legal business information, addresses, account email contacts and brand assets used across Marketplacer-managed Seller interfaces, emails and documents.","audience":["Marketplace operations","Environment Managers","Brand and marketing","Finance","Customer service","Technology"],"sections":{"Understanding Site Details and Branding":"<p>Use three configuration areas to establish the marketplace identity:</p><div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Navigation</th><th>Purpose</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Configuration > Site Details</td><td>Marketplace name, business details, address and Account Emails</td></tr><tr><td>Configuration > Customisation Settings</td><td>Standard Logo, Email Logo and favicon</td></tr><tr><td>Configuration > Language Customisation</td><td>Supported Seller-facing email, invoice and refund wording</td></tr></tbody></table></div><p>Marketplacer branding applies to Marketplacer-managed Seller interfaces, communications and documents. Configure the customer-facing ecommerce website separately and align the approved marketplace name, logo, legal details and support contacts.</p><div class=\"contextual-walkthroughs\"><h3>Platform walkthrough</h3><a class=\"contextual-walkthrough-link\" href=\"https://www.loom.com/share/36a69e007d884d03b2e85a3b79393c93?sid=66370e37-af11-41b1-a345-81a9b07840d3\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><span>Site Details</span><strong>Watch walkthrough</strong></a></div>","Business Details":"<p>Navigate to <code>Configuration &gt; Site Details</code>.</p><h3>Site Name</h3><p>Use the approved marketplace or trading name, as the Site Name is used across Marketplacer interfaces, emails, documents, reports and integration responses.</p><h3>Site URL</h3><p>Enter the customer-facing marketplace URL, not the Marketplacer administration URL.</p><h3>Official Business Name</h3><p>Enter the legal entity operating the marketplace. This may appear on invoices and billing documents.</p><h3>Business Registration Number</h3><p>Add the relevant ABN, company number or regional registration identifier where required by Finance or Legal.</p>","Address and Country":"<h3>Multi-Line Address</h3><p>Use the formatted business address displayed on applicable tax and billing documents.</p><h3>Street Address</h3><p>Use the address format required for Order invoices and related marketplace documents.</p><h3>Country</h3><p>Select the marketplace country carefully because it can influence tax, currency, address formatting and regional platform behaviour.</p><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Confirm the legal entity and address with Finance or Legal</li><li>Keep both address fields consistent unless an approved document requirement differs</li><li>Generate representative documents and review the presentation</li><li>Assess impact with Marketplacer before changing Country after implementation begins</li></ul>","Account Emails":"<p>Navigate to <code>Configuration &gt; Site Details &gt; Account Emails</code>.</p><div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Field</th><th>Typical use</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Auditable-edit notifications</td><td>Alerts when sensitive Seller data changes</td></tr><tr><td>Info Email Address</td><td>Main sender or recipient for selected correspondence</td></tr><tr><td>Accounts Email Address</td><td>Billing, Remittance and finance-related messages</td></tr><tr><td>Order Copy Email Addresses</td><td>Internal copies of Marketplacer-generated Order emails</td></tr><tr><td>Remittance Copy Email Addresses</td><td>Copies of Remittance notifications and summaries</td></tr><tr><td>No-reply Email Address</td><td>Automated messages not intended for replies</td></tr><tr><td>Customer Support Email Address</td><td>Customer-service visibility for selected refund notices</td></tr><tr><td>Staging Email CC</td><td>Internal copy of intercepted Sandbox emails</td></tr></tbody></table></div><p>Use monitored functional inboxes where a team owns the process. The Emails and Notifications page covers message ownership, suppression and testing in detail.</p>","Branding Assets":"<p>Navigate to <code>Configuration &gt; Customisation Settings</code>.</p><div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Asset</th><th>Practical guidance</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Standard Logo</td><td>Use the approved marketplace logo for Seller-facing Marketplacer interfaces</td></tr><tr><td>Email Logo</td><td>Use a clear PNG that renders well on a white or transparent background</td></tr><tr><td>Favicon</td><td>Use a simplified square mark that remains readable at browser-tab size</td></tr></tbody></table></div><p>Keep the approved source files in a controlled brand repository. Upload the assets in Sandbox, review the result and then apply the approved version in Production.</p>","Where Branding Appears":"<h3>Seller Portal</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Login and portal navigation</li><li>Dashboard and account pages</li><li>Product, Order and refund areas</li></ul><h3>Emails and PDFs</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Welcome and password emails</li><li>Order and refund notifications</li><li>Remittance communications</li><li>Invoices and other generated PDF documents</li></ul><h3>Ecommerce front end</h3><p>Configure customer-facing logo, favicon, typography, navigation and email templates in the ecommerce or content platform. Align them with the Marketplacer identity without assuming one system updates the other.</p>","Language and Brand Voice":"<p>Navigate to <code>Configuration &gt; Language Customisation</code> to update supported platform wording.</p><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Confirm approved terms such as Seller, product, Order, cancellation, return and Remittance</li><li>Retain accurate Marketplacer record names where they refer to specific platform objects</li><li>Preserve variables, placeholders, links and HTML in templates</li><li>Test the complete email or document after every change</li><li>Maintain a register of keys, approved wording and environment status</li></ul>","Production and Sandbox Setup":"<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Sandbox</th><th>Production</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Test logos, language, emails and generated documents</td><td>Use final approved identity and legal details</td></tr><tr><td>Configure Staging Email CC</td><td>Use live monitored email addresses</td></tr><tr><td>Use an approved staging front-end URL where required</td><td>Use the live marketplace URL</td></tr><tr><td>Review test-specific suppression</td><td>Confirm live notification ownership</td></tr></tbody></table></div><h3>Verify before launch</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Site Name and Site URL</li><li>Legal business name, registration number and addresses</li><li>Country</li><li>Account Emails</li><li>Standard Logo, Email Logo and favicon</li><li>Language Customisation</li><li>Seller Portal, email and PDF rendering</li></ul><h3>Related Marketplacer articles</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/360037668712-Site-Details\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Site Details</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/360001859151-Branding-options-in-Customisation-Settings\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Branding options in Customisation Settings</a></li></ul>"},"related":[["emails-notifications","Emails and Notifications"],["sendgrid","SendGrid Whitelabelling"],["production-readiness","Production Readiness"]]},"emails-notifications":{"summary":"Configure email addresses and notification ownership, prevent duplicate messages across connected systems, test Sandbox routing and use the Mail Sending Log to investigate delivery issues.","audience":["Marketplace operations","Customer service","Seller management","Finance","Technology and integrations","Brand and marketing"],"sections":{"Understanding Marketplace Emails and Notifications":"<p>Emails may be generated by Marketplacer, your ecommerce platform, customer-service platform, payment provider, Seller systems or integration services. Define ownership before enabling or suppressing messages.</p><div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Confirm for every message</th><th>Examples</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Trigger</td><td>Seller created, Order created, Shipment, Refund Request or Remittance</td></tr><tr><td>Recipient</td><td>Seller, customer, Operator or internal team</td></tr><tr><td>Sending system</td><td>Marketplacer, ecommerce, CRM, payment provider or Seller system</td></tr><tr><td>Sender and reply address</td><td>Approved functional address</td></tr><tr><td>Monitoring owner</td><td>Marketplace operations, customer service, finance or technology</td></tr></tbody></table></div><p>Create a communication map for welcome emails, Orders, Shipments, refunds, Remittances and integration alerts.</p>","Account Email Addresses":"<p>Navigate to <code>Configuration &gt; Site Details &gt; Account Emails</code>.</p><div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Field</th><th>Recommended ownership</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Auditable-edit notifications</td><td>Marketplace controls or Finance</td></tr><tr><td>Info Email Address</td><td>Customer service or marketplace operations</td></tr><tr><td>Accounts Email Address</td><td>Finance</td></tr><tr><td>Order Copy Email Addresses</td><td>Marketplace operations</td></tr><tr><td>Remittance Copy Email Addresses</td><td>Finance</td></tr><tr><td>No-reply Email Address</td><td>Technology or digital operations</td></tr><tr><td>Customer Support Email Address</td><td>Customer service</td></tr><tr><td>Staging Email CC</td><td>Sandbox testing owner</td></tr></tbody></table></div><p>Use monitored functional inboxes where the process belongs to a team. Confirm sender-domain authentication through SendGrid whitelabelling before live email testing.</p>","Seller Notifications":"<p>Review account, Order, refund and Remittance contacts when creating or editing a Seller under <code>Sellers &gt; Manage Sellers &gt; Edit Seller</code>.</p><h3>Confirm how the Seller receives Orders</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Marketplacer email and Seller Portal</li><li>MConnect</li><li>Seller API or webhook</li><li>Another connected order-management system</li></ul><p>An integrated Seller may use its source platform as the primary operational workspace. Decide whether Marketplacer email remains a useful fallback or creates duplicate messages.</p><h3>Refund and Remittance notifications</h3><p>Review marketplace-wide controls under <code>Configuration &gt; Seller Settings</code>. Suppress a Marketplacer notification only after the replacement process covers every required event and escalation.</p>","Customer Notifications and Connected Systems":"<p>Define the sending system for account, Order, dispatch, cancellation, return and refund messages.</p><div class=\"process-flow\"><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">1</span><strong>Marketplacer records the marketplace event</strong></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">2</span><strong>The connected system receives the status</strong></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">3</span><strong>The approved customer platform sends the message</strong></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">4</span><strong>Customer service monitors the outcome</strong></div></div><p>Test partial Shipments, cancellations, returns and refunds to confirm the customer receives one accurate message from the intended system.</p><div class=\"callout note\"><strong>Coordinate refund communication with payment processing.</strong> Finalising the Marketplacer Refund Request updates marketplace records. The customer payment refund follows the approved payment-provider process.</div>","Sandbox Email Routing":"<p>Sandbox emails are intercepted so test activity does not contact live recipients. Configure:</p><p><code>Configuration &gt; Site Details &gt; Account Emails &gt; Staging Email CC</code></p><p>The nominated inbox receives copies of welcome, password, recovery, Order, refund, Remittance and other test emails.</p><ol><li>Confirm the Staging Email CC before creating a user.</li><li>Trigger the test email.</li><li>Locate it in the nominated inbox.</li><li>Forward account-access messages only to the approved tester.</li><li>Verify the content, branding and links.</li><li>Protect password and recovery information.</li></ol><p>After a Sandbox refresh, recheck the field and run an account-email smoke test.</p>","Email Suppression and Duplicate Prevention":"<p>Site Details contains controls to skip emails to Sellers or consumers. Seller Settings also includes more targeted notification controls.</p><h3>Before suppressing a message</h3><ol><li>Record the approved communication owner.</li><li>Test the replacement message.</li><li>Confirm operational monitoring and escalation.</li><li>Apply the setting in Sandbox.</li><li>Run the complete workflow.</li><li>Verify one correct message reaches the recipient.</li><li>Apply and validate the Production setting.</li></ol><div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Communication</th><th>Possible owner</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Seller welcome</td><td>Marketplacer</td></tr><tr><td>Seller new Order</td><td>Marketplacer or Seller integration</td></tr><tr><td>Customer Order confirmation</td><td>Ecommerce platform</td></tr><tr><td>Customer dispatch</td><td>Ecommerce platform</td></tr><tr><td>Seller Refund Request</td><td>Marketplacer</td></tr><tr><td>Customer refund confirmation</td><td>Customer-service or ecommerce platform</td></tr><tr><td>Seller Remittance advice</td><td>Marketplacer or payout process</td></tr></tbody></table></div>","Language Customisation":"<p>Navigate to <code>Configuration &gt; Language Customisation</code>.</p><ol><li>Search by key or existing wording.</li><li>Select the edit icon.</li><li>Apply the approved text.</li><li>Preserve variables, placeholders, links and HTML.</li><li>Save and allow the update to refresh.</li><li>Generate the complete message or document.</li><li>Review the result in Sandbox before Production.</li></ol><p>Check subject, greeting, marketplace name, Seller terminology, links, instructions, support contact, footer and mobile rendering.</p>","Testing, Monitoring and Troubleshooting":"<h3>Test representative messages</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Operator and Seller welcome emails</li><li>Password reset and recovery codes</li><li>New Order and partial Shipment</li><li>Cancellation and return</li><li>Refund finalised</li><li>Remittance notification and summary</li><li>Auditable Seller-data change</li></ul><h3>Mail Sending Log</h3><p>Navigate to <code>Reporting &gt; Mail Sending Log</code> to confirm whether Marketplacer generated a transactional email, the recipient and the relevant timestamp.</p><h3>Missing-email sequence</h3><ol><li>Confirm the environment and event.</li><li>Confirm which system owns the message.</li><li>Check the recipient address.</li><li>Check Staging Email CC for Sandbox.</li><li>Check the Mail Sending Log.</li><li>Check spam and quarantine.</li><li>Confirm SendGrid verification.</li><li>Review suppression and Seller-specific settings.</li><li>Collect evidence and submit a Support request where required.</li></ol><h3>Related Marketplacer articles</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/360037668712-Site-Details\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Site Details</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/360027481052-Language-Customisation\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Language Customisation</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/25930591592973-Seller-settings\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Seller settings</a></li></ul>"},"related":[["site-branding","Site Details and Branding"],["sendgrid","SendGrid Whitelabelling"],["integration-troubleshooting","Integration Troubleshooting"]]},"sendgrid":{"summary":"Add the CNAME records supplied by your Marketplacer Delivery Manager, verify the domain in the Operator Portal and test Marketplacer-generated transactional emails.","audience":["Marketplace operations","Environment Managers","DNS or domain administrators","Technology","Brand teams"],"sections":{"What SendGrid Whitelabelling Does":"<p>Marketplacer uses SendGrid for transactional emails such as account access, Order, refund and Remittance notifications. Whitelabelling authorises Marketplacer to send these emails using your approved domain and helps reduce spam or junk classification.</p><p>This setup applies to Marketplacer-generated transactional emails. Marketing campaigns and customer lifecycle email tools are configured separately.</p>","Receive the CNAME Records":"<p>Your Marketplacer Delivery Manager generates the required records under:</p><p><code>Configuration &gt; Sendgrid Whitelabel Domains</code></p><p>They will email the records to you. You can also view them on the same page in the Operator Portal.</p><div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Field</th><th>What you receive</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Host Name</td><td>The DNS hostname to add</td></tr><tr><td>Record Type</td><td>CNAME</td></tr><tr><td>Data</td><td>The SendGrid destination value</td></tr></tbody></table></div><p>Forward the records to the person or team that manages your domain where you do not have direct access.</p>","Add the CNAME Records":"<p>Add every supplied record to your domain provider, such as Cloudflare, GoDaddy, Crazy Domains or your organisation’s DNS-management platform.</p><ol><li>Open the DNS records for the domain.</li><li>Create a CNAME record.</li><li>Copy the supplied Host Name exactly.</li><li>Copy the supplied Data or target exactly.</li><li>Save the record.</li><li>Repeat for each CNAME.</li></ol><div class=\"callout note\"><strong>Use the exact records supplied for your marketplace.</strong> CNAME values are unique. Avoid copying records from another marketplace, environment or email provider.</div>","Verify the Setup":"<p>After adding the records:</p><ol><li>Return to <strong>Configuration &gt; Sendgrid Whitelabel Domains</strong>.</li><li>Locate the domain.</li><li>Click the middle <strong>Verify</strong> button.</li><li>Confirm the page shows <strong>Verified? TRUE</strong>.</li></ol><p>DNS changes may take time to update. Where the domain does not verify immediately, wait for propagation and try again.</p>","Test Your Emails":"<p>After verification, test representative Marketplacer emails.</p><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Operator or Seller welcome email</li><li>Password reset</li><li>Order notification</li><li>Refund notification</li><li>Remittance notification</li><li>Email with an Invoice or other attachment</li></ul><p>Confirm the correct sender, marketplace name, Email Logo, recipient, links and inbox delivery. In Sandbox, review copied emails through <code>Configuration &gt; Site Details &gt; Account Emails &gt; Staging Email CC</code>.</p><p>Use <code>Reporting &gt; Mail Sending Log</code> to confirm whether Marketplacer generated the message.</p>","Troubleshooting":"<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Issue</th><th>Check</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Verified remains FALSE</td><td>All CNAMEs are present, Host and Data values are exact, the provider has not duplicated the domain suffix and DNS propagation has completed</td></tr><tr><td>Email reaches junk</td><td>Sender alignment, content, recipient quarantine and domain reputation</td></tr><tr><td>Email is missing</td><td>Environment, Staging Email CC, Mail Sending Log, suppression settings and recipient address</td></tr><tr><td>DNS administrator reports a conflict</td><td>Existing record at the same hostname and any other SendGrid configuration using the domain</td></tr></tbody></table></div><p>Include the marketplace, environment, domain, CNAME values, verification status, email type, recipient, timestamp and troubleshooting in a Support request.</p><h3>Related Marketplacer articles</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/4402837795853-Sendgrid-Whitelabels\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Sendgrid Whitelabels</a></li></ul>"},"related":[["emails-notifications","Emails and Notifications"],["site-branding","Site Details and Branding"],["getting-support","Getting Support"]]},"configuration-overview":{"summary":"Use the Operator Portal configuration map, understand marketplace-wide defaults and Seller-level exceptions, and complete setup in an order that supports Seller onboarding, testing and launch.","audience":["Marketplace operations","Environment Managers","Project leads","Finance","Catalogue","Seller management","Customer service","Technology"],"sections":{"Understanding Marketplace Configuration":"<p>Use <strong>Configuration</strong> for access, identity, Seller defaults, product controls, finance, communications, refunds, shipping and integrations. Use <strong>Categorisation</strong> for Categories, Brands, Prototypes and Option Types. Use Sellers, Adverts, Orders and Reporting for day-to-day operations.</p><p>Configuration translates approved marketplace decisions into platform behaviour.</p><div class=\"process-flow\"><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">1</span><strong>Approve the policy or commercial position</strong></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">2</span><strong>Apply the related Marketplacer settings</strong></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">3</span><strong>Test the complete workflow</strong></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">4</span><strong>Record the Production result</strong></div></div><p>The menu may vary according to enabled features and the user’s role.</p>","Configuration Menu Map":"<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Area</th><th>Current navigation examples</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Identity and communications</td><td>Site Details, Customisation Settings, Language Customisation, Sendgrid Whitelabel Domains</td></tr><tr><td>Access and authentication</td><td>Authentication Settings, SSO Configuration, SSO Identity Providers, User Roles & Permissions</td></tr><tr><td>Seller defaults</td><td>Seller Settings, Seller Onboarding Processes</td></tr><tr><td>Products</td><td>Product Settings > Advert Settings, Golden Product Settings, External Account Settings</td></tr><tr><td>Finance</td><td>Finance Settings, Commission Packages, Commission Package Scheduling, MPay Settings, Payment Methods</td></tr><tr><td>Shipping and refunds</td><td>Shipping Settings, Shipment Carriers, Refund Reasons</td></tr><tr><td>Integrations</td><td>Apps and Integrations, Marketplacer API Keys, OAuth Clients, Webhooks</td></tr></tbody></table></div><p>Product Vetting and Catalog Rules are managed under <strong>Adverts</strong>. Categories, Brands, Prototypes and Option Types are managed under <strong>Categorisation</strong>.</p><div class=\"contextual-walkthroughs\"><h3>Configuration walkthroughs</h3><a class=\"contextual-walkthrough-link\" href=\"https://www.loom.com/share/f3f9756e3c2246939072e1a483ad831c?sid=d4388905-cf67-4ce3-8480-29e35284e503\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><span>Account Settings</span><strong>Watch walkthrough</strong></a><a class=\"contextual-walkthrough-link\" href=\"https://www.loom.com/share/2923ca928e934b099b036e5dbb865489?sid=e9604da3-c6c7-4088-88a7-7f0a8949f6de\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><span>Advert Settings</span><strong>Watch walkthrough</strong></a><a class=\"contextual-walkthrough-link\" href=\"https://www.loom.com/share/956f1c5c4df346aa95f4cc9d25a16eb2?sid=3fbe255d-49fd-4f7d-aa15-586564cf576a\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><span>Seller Settings</span><strong>Watch walkthrough</strong></a></div>","Marketplace-Wide and Seller-Level Settings":"<p>Use marketplace-wide settings for the standard operating position. Apply a Seller-level value only where an approved commercial or operational arrangement requires an exception.</p><div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Area</th><th>Marketplace-wide</th><th>Seller-level example</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Dispatch SLA</td><td>Configuration > Seller Settings</td><td>Seller-specific SLA</td></tr><tr><td>Remittance delay</td><td>Seller Settings > Subscriptions and Charges</td><td>Manage Sellers > Edit Seller > Remittance Details</td></tr><tr><td>Commission</td><td>Create Commission Packages</td><td>Assign a package to the Seller</td></tr><tr><td>Product vetting</td><td>Advert Vetting attributes</td><td>Require all products to be vetted</td></tr><tr><td>Refunds</td><td>Refund Reasons and workflow policy</td><td>Seller cancellation and refund permissions</td></tr><tr><td>Shipping</td><td>Shipping Rules and Profiles</td><td>Seller Zones and Rates where permitted</td></tr></tbody></table></div><p>Record the standard position, approved exception, decision owner, effective date and review date.</p>","Recommended Configuration Sequence":"<ol><li>Environment access, team members, roles, authentication and SSO</li><li>Site Details, branding, Account Emails, Language Customisation and SendGrid</li><li>Seller defaults and performance SLAs</li><li>Tax, commission, wholesale, merchant fees, Remittances and payments</li><li>Option Types, Prototypes, Categories and Brands</li><li>Advert Settings, mapping, Catalog Rules, product vetting and Golden Products</li><li>Shipping Rules, Profiles, Zones, Rates and Shipment Carriers</li><li>Refund Reasons, Seller permissions and refund financial treatment</li><li>APIs, webhooks, MConnect, monitoring and manual fallback</li><li>End-to-end testing and Production verification</li></ol><p>This order reduces rework. For example, complete taxonomy before live product ingestion, Shipping Profiles before Variant assignment and Commission Packages before assigning live Sellers.</p>","Configuration Dependencies":"<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Dependency</th><th>Why it matters</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Roles before implementation</td><td>Users need the correct access to configure and test</td></tr><tr><td>Branding and email before invitations</td><td>Sellers and users should receive approved identity and communication</td></tr><tr><td>Taxonomy before products</td><td>Prototype and attribute requirements depend on Category</td></tr><tr><td>Shipping Profiles before Variants</td><td>Variants must reference an existing Profile</td></tr><tr><td>Commission Packages before live Sellers</td><td>Seller configuration should match approved terms from the start</td></tr><tr><td>Refund Reasons before workflow testing</td><td>Cancellation and return scenarios need the correct reason types</td></tr><tr><td>Integration ownership before credentials</td><td>Keys and webhooks require an owner, destination, monitoring and removal process</td></tr></tbody></table></div>","Testing and Applying Changes":"<p>Use this standard flow:</p><ol><li>Confirm the decision.</li><li>Configure in Sandbox.</li><li>Test the operational outcome.</li><li>Approve the result.</li><li>Apply it in Production.</li><li>Verify the live workflow.</li><li>Retain evidence.</li></ol><div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Setting changed</th><th>Workflow to test</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Commission Package</td><td>Create an Order and review commission</td></tr><tr><td>Refund Reason</td><td>Create and finalise the relevant Refund Request</td></tr><tr><td>Shipping Rate</td><td>Run a checkout scenario</td></tr><tr><td>Product-vetting trigger</td><td>Change the monitored Advert field</td></tr><tr><td>Staging Email CC</td><td>Create or reset a Sandbox user</td></tr><tr><td>Webhook</td><td>Trigger the subscribed event and inspect delivery</td></tr><tr><td>Language Customisation</td><td>Generate the complete email or document</td></tr></tbody></table></div><div class=\"callout warning\"><strong>Review high-impact settings before Production.</strong> Tax model, finance configuration, marketplace-wide email suppression and other broad controls can affect existing Sellers, products and financial records.</div>","Maintaining a Configuration Register":"<p>Record the approved position and implementation evidence for every launch-critical setting.</p><div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Field</th><th>Purpose</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Configuration area and navigation path</td><td>Shows where the setting is managed</td></tr><tr><td>Approved position and decision owner</td><td>Connects policy to configuration</td></tr><tr><td>Configuration owner</td><td>Identifies who applies the change</td></tr><tr><td>Sandbox and Production status</td><td>Tracks testing and live implementation</td></tr><tr><td>Seller exceptions</td><td>Records approved variations</td></tr><tr><td>Evidence and last review date</td><td>Supports audit, support and handover</td></tr></tbody></table></div><p>The register should connect the marketplace decision, setting, Sandbox test, Production result and operational procedure.</p>","Pre-Launch Review and Ongoing Governance":"<h3>Before launch</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Access and Full Admin review</li><li>Site Details, branding and email verification</li><li>Seller defaults and performance SLAs</li><li>Tax, Commission Packages, Remittances and payout process</li><li>Taxonomy, product governance and mapping</li><li>Shipping and tracking</li><li>Cancellation, return and refund workflows</li><li>Production integrations, monitoring and fallbacks</li><li>Controlled end-to-end tests</li></ul><h3>After launch</h3><p>Review configuration when policies change, Seller exceptions are approved, new categories or payment processes are introduced, integrations change, incidents identify a control gap or ownership changes.</p><h3>Related Marketplacer articles</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/29056159273101-Operator-portal-quick-start-guide-videos\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Operator Portal quick start guide videos</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/25930591592973-Seller-settings\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Seller settings</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/28925785268365-Operator-user-role-permissions\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Operator user role permissions</a></li></ul>"},"related":[["production-sandbox","Production and Sandbox"],["marketplace-decision-register","Marketplace Decision Register"],["configuration-testing","Marketplace Configuration Testing"]]}};
